Definition.WordDefinition: analog adj : of a circuit or device having an output that is proportional to the input; "analogue device"; "linear amplifier" [syn: {analogue}, {linear}] [ant: {digital}] n : something having the property of being analogous to something else [syn: {analogue}, {parallel}]
